cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper presents a scalable algorithm for learning parametric constraints from expert demonstrations, which involves solving an integer program in the parameter space. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). Among these, machine learning and robotics are the most likely sub-categories as the paper focuses on learning constraints from demonstrations for high-dimensional systems.
